{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' task-plans/claude-codex-team-space-task-plan.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Claude Codex Team Space Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 3\n\n## Objective\n\nExpand from Codex-only control into a provider-aware agent team workspace.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Claude + Codex shared board\n- provider-aware role separation\n- collaboration model across providers\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Provider Abstraction\n\n- define provider-neutral thread/task concepts\n- keep provider-specific actions isolated\n\n### Task 2 — Shared Team Surface\n\n- decide how Codex and Claude entities coexist in one board or team space\n- keep visual semantics clear across providers\n\n### Task 3 — Role and Ownership Model\n\n- define how work is split between providers\n- avoid pretending provider internals are fully controllable\n\n## Constraints\n\nOfficial provider plugins do not expose full internal APIs. This phase must be designed as coordination, not total provider control.\n\n## Exit Criteria\n\n- a realistic shared team-space model exists\n- the design respects provider boundaries\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
